One officer was arrested for accepting a bribe from an undercover anti-corruption officer. JOHANNESBURG - Two Gauteng metro police officers are in court today for two separate incidents of bribery and shoplifting. One officer was arrested for accepting a bribe from an undercover anti-corruption officer. The other officer allegedly failed to pay for items he had taken from a shop in the Springs area. Police spokesperson Kay Makhubele says officers found to be on the wrong side of the law will not be spared. The two officers who were arrested from metro police on Saturday for bribery and shop lifting will be appearing at the Springs Magistrates Court. (Edited by Neo Koza)